ont></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/beqasylum.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=worthy>Worthy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/14/00 9:08:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Weapons for Clerics</span><hr size=1> I hit a situation the other night in Kanor, and, I would like the input of my fellow healers.<br>
First, for the record, I like to melee. As long as I am FM, Buffed, and full HP, I will jump into the Frey, and add my Cad of Sacrament's blunt head to my foe's Blunt head.(hehe)<br>
<br>
I do this for three reasons:<br>
<br>
  1) Any Extra damage done to the Mob makes it die that much faster!!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
  2) Melee increases my fighting skills. My 1HB is 169, and my Offence is 199. (Not bad for a 42nd level Cleric)<br>
<br>
  3) I like to get HIT, because, that increases my Defence rating! That gives me better armor class. That means I am harder to hit when the mobs argo on me for casting that C-Heal. It also gives me room for more wisdom based items, that might take away from my normal Armor Class.(Right now, with buffs, my ac is around the mid 700's, and, that is WITH 189 Wisdom, and Cad of Sacrament in hand)<br>
<br>
Now, as to what happened the other night in Kanor. Our party beat up the Drov Captain, and, he dropped a Jade Mace. The weapon is 9/18.<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.everlore.com/items/items.asp?mode=show&IID=129891">www.everlore.com/items/it...IID=129891</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> Very Nice.<br>
<br>
When a Cleric is OOM, and, he cannot med, if he cannot fight, he is nothing.<br>
 <br>
As we were about to roll, one of the Warriors said that I should not be allowed to roll for it, because, I was ONLY a cleric, and, weapons are toys for me. That I should only worry about Wisdom items, just sit back and heal. Only a class like a Warrior or such should get it. <br>
<br>
I felt that I should have the same opportunity to roll for this fine weapon. I was not asking for preference, just the same chance as every one else.  I did end up getting to roll, the group voted in my favor. I lost the roll, but, at least I got to try for it.<br>
<br>
I would like input from my fellow healers.  I know some choose NOT to melee, but, does that exclude us from getting one of the few real nice weapons that we can use?<br>
<br>
Thanks for your time.<br>
<br>
Worthy Iam<br>
Officer, Chosen Counsel.<br>
