<br>
Well well well ... this is topical for me.<br>
<br>
Tonight in Karnor, I was in a pick-up group and the Jade Mace dropped. It was decided (I was not the group leader, the leader was a warrior, and a very nice person as well) that all six people could roll on it (WAR WAR CLR ROG BRD DRU). I was lucky enough to win the roll and so the Jade Mace was given to me.<br>
<br>
I was *very* happy. Not because I was thinking &quot;Gee I can sell this for megabucks&quot;. That's not me at all. But because I was thinking &quot;Now I am one step closer being able to roleplay the battle cleric I always wanted&quot;. Yes I know Verant have stuffed Clerics on the melee front and all the rest of what is said above, but this doesn't mean I have to buy into it; if I want to build the best melee-capable cleric I am able I can and will do so, as it is all part of the self-image of the character I love. If someone else thinks differently, well, do as you like with your own character is what I say.<br>
<br>
Now I will permanently carry around with me my Jade Mace, my Springwood Club and my Cone of the Mystics, to interchange between them for given circumstances.<br>
<br>
I'm glad the group I was in when it dropped didn't have any of the pre-conceived opinions represented in a couple of places here on this thread (and elsewhere), or I'd not have met my aim this evening or been as happy when I logged tonight.<br>
<br>
On the general point tho, I have this to say. I broadly support 'Need before Greed', i.e., Warrior-only item goes to a warrior in the group if there is one present and he has not got it and would equip it if he had it.<br>
<br>
But if the item drops that is multi-class, where members of more than one class who *could* use it are present, and those members *would* equip it if they were to get it, then members of all those classes should get an equal roll. This is my view and I'd enforce it if I were group leader, as to arbitrarily exclude one class for some judgement reason that class A could make more use of it than class B is unfair in my books.<br>
<br>
This means whether it be a Jade Mace or a Springwood Club, a cleric and a warrior should both get a roll on both if they would equip them (not if all they were going to do was sell them mind you). This allows characters to have their own aspirations (god forbid a bit of roleplaying!) to equip themselves as they so please.<br>
<br>
Thank you and goodnight.<br>
<br>
Felishanna Secretlight<br>
